text: Mike Pence talks a good game as far as bipartisanship but I met with their team 21 times to make tax cuts larger & permanent for the middle class, not big businesses and millionaires. They decided to be strictly partisan instead of helping the middle class West Virginians.

I am shocked that after the @VP worked for almost a year in a divisive & partisan way to take healthcare away from almost 200k WVians, bankrupt our hospitals & push tax cuts for the wealthiest Americans & huge corporations that he would come to #WV & continue partisan attacks.
As someone who sees the impacts the opioid epidemic is having on @huntingtoncity every day I’m glad @POTUS pledged to continue fighting! #SOTU

I’m proud the bipartisan group of Senators @SenatorCollins & I assembled have worked out a compromise to end the #shutdown & reopen the government. Vote coming soon.

Funding the government is one of our most basic constitutional obligations & now because of partisan politics, the government will shut down. Governing this way is dangerous to our national security and embarrassing for both political parties.
I have never & will never vote to shutdown the government.

Today I cosponsored legislation to overturn the @FCC's repeal of the #NetNeutrality rule. I've heard from thousands of WVians who want an internet that is free of content-based discrimination & support increased reliable, affordable internet access throughout our state.

Today we honor Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., one of our nation’s most influential & inspiring leaders of all time. As we remember his life & his legacy today, I want to remind all West Virginians that we are all capable of making a difference. #MLKDay

I’m saddened to learn of the passing of Paul Nyden. Paul was a giant at @wvgazettemail & the impact of his work was felt across #WV & Appalachia. His relentless search for truth & commitment to his craft set the bar for what responsible investigative journalism looks like.

12 years ago, 12 brave miners tragically lost their lives at Sago. On that day, I grieved with the miners’ families & with all WVians. I think of those miners & the strength & sacrifices of their families each & every day, & my thoughts & prayers are with them & their loved ones.

All of #WV is heartbroken to learn of the loss of Thurman A. Watts. Yet again, we are reminded of the incredible sacrifices our coal miners & their families make. Gayle & I join the entire state in sending our thoughts & prayers to the Watts family during this difficult time.
Merry Christmas from Gayle & I to all West Virginians, Americans & our brave service men & women!

CHIP ensures 21k #WV children have healthcare access. I want to hear from my fellow West Virginians about the difference #CHIP makes in your lives. Send your stories & family photos to CHIP@manchin.senate.gov & I'll share them on the Senate floor.

businesses & explodes our debt.
